While I agree with a previous commenter who noted that there is so much to do in real life, I disagree that these games are "time wasters" for toddlers. Let's face it: technology isn't likely to decline anytime soon, if anything its on the rise, with every generation seeming to start using technology earlier than the last. Much like parents in the generation that birthed the television, parents of young children today can't help but see the inherent dangers in allowing children to become addicted or overly reliant on technology. I know that its a concern of mine. I am, however, a pragmatist. Technology exists, our children will be exposed to it, and our goal should be to ensure moderation and that what they are exposed to is enriching, positive and entertaining. Sooo... a time waster? Perhaps that's one way of looking at it. But I believe in balance, so adding these games to my toddlers educational apps hasn't felt like a waste of time at all. The incessant giggling sago mini games elicit from her confirms my feelings. Yes, there is much to see and do in the real world. Sometimes it is easy to forget that technology is part of that world, and that it has its place. And that much of the everyday, mundane tasks we perform are simply boring, for us and our children: waiting in lines, sitting in waiting rooms, buckled into a carseat for long trips... at these times, i am grateful to the game designers who have created thoughtful, imaginative "time wasters" for our children to discover and enjoy.

My 3.5 year-old has loved playing this app for over a year with no loss of interest in sight. This farm app is great because all elements (animals, fruits and veggies, farm equipment) interact with each other in seemingly endless ways that foster creativity and ensure no session with it will be the same as any other. We have a number of Sago Mini games and have found them all to be creative, well made, and not filled with ads or inappropriate content. This one is probably the favorite one the bunch because it's so open-ended and interesting.
